ol.li: Non-blocking: printk() can be called from any context (irq, atomic).
Sequence IDs: Readers track next_seq to detect dropped messages.
Wrap-around: When head == tail, oldest entries are dropped.
Filtering: console_log_level is typically set via sysctl or cmdline.
